No doubt LC, to each his/her own. My point is no matter what you believe their is a reality out there that encompasses all dispositions (even some we cannot begin to understand). I am aware of spirit rescue but I am also aware that each individual spirit has to tow their own load. Some are not able to understand or handle the next step without going through what they are going through. I have been told to protect the innocent and help only when asked. 

As for the light, we have been told through not only many years of  ITC but also many years of mediumistic contacts that the source of existence is the light (what many consider to be God). Some of us shine brighter than others but we are not considered the light, although I think we may refer to ourselves, &quot;of the light&quot;.

I will always follow the philosophy that it is better to learn to deal with all aspects of the beings we contact whether you consider them negative or positive (both concepts are relative). Always remember, you cannot fear what you love. Below is a quote from the only &quot;technician&quot; I have ever heard of:

&quot;It is the way of morals,
which means to understand, to acknowledge, to devise, and to act. It is not to
be mixed up with religion, which means to believe. However, the two can be
complementary. But they are independent one from the other.&quot;

Regards,

Frank R.

